g.text: Look who's online. Anything you want to talk about?

g.text: So. What's on Aoi's mind today?

g.text: how kind of u to ask! I'd love to know more about Duviri, if ur willing to share

g.text: how kind of u to ask! I'd love to know more about Lotus, if ur willing to share

g.title: j2224108448
g.text: how kind of u to ask! i was wondering about Duviri, if ur willing to share

g.title: j3195716957
g.text: Sure. I mean... I don't know her very well? The kid knows her better than I do. But she saved my life.

g.title: j700478403
g.text: I owed her for saving my life. So when she needed me to come here, I answered the call.

g.title: j2226599820
g.text: Heh. Right, well, you remember those literal dragons I told you about? That's where they were.

g.title: j2789873011
g.text: Duviri can be beautiful but it's... also dangerous, like all storybook worlds. Filled with monsters and lessons to learn.

g.title: j965588550
g.text: You'll get a kick out of this. Duviri has flying dragons, called Orowyrms.

g.title: j34439381
g.text: oh? how did she save u?

g.title: j1263726177
g.text: i really want to see them they sound SO COOL

g.title: j2638881833
g.text: A version of me from this timeline that didn't age because they were stuck in a stasis pod on Lua, which the Lotus, who later saved me, put Lua and the kid into the Void for a while, to keep everybody safe--

g.title: j3996156312
g.text: Right. Yeah. So. Technically, I'm from an alternate timeline. The other version of me didn't age as much, because... y'know? It's a long story.

g.title: j287588913
g.text: When I was in Duviri, I was... trapped. In apathy. I'd forgotten who I was. Why I was there.

g.title: j3018154200
g.text: Sometimes, when you're stuck at the bottom of your life... you just need a helping hand.

g.title: j4087297687
g.text: You know how I can use Transference to steer you around? I can use Transference on an Orowyrm, too. That is *really* weird.

g.title: j3779291085
g.text: They can be, when they're not trying to kill you.

g.title: j1412976730
g.text: We have an evil child king, named Dominus Thrax.

g.title: j2294837666
g.text: We have a full court of characters, each plagued by their own horrible backstories. Each one represents an emotion.

g.title: j28057630
g.text: I'll tell that one to you in person over drinks.

g.title: j2137285379
g.text: And she was one of the two people who helped pull me out of there.

g.title: j748664214
g.text: And she gave me one. Literally.

g.title: j2368790683
g.text: but they sound like they'd be fun to fight, though

g.title: j52570318
g.text: aww... is he really evil tho?

g.title: j3314992028
g.text: lol sounds like a lot, yeah

g.title: j453798028
g.text: The Lotus and Teshin, my mentor, are the reason why I had the ability and the bravery to escape that place.

g.title: j2859081280
g.text: what's it like to be a dragon?!?!

g.title: j2852759261
g.text: He can't help the way the Void made him.

g.title: j1061611355
g.text: To put it lightly. But they're the closest thing I ever really had to family that I can really remember...?

g.title: j3121880713
g.text: Eh. It's all a metaphor for learning to accept and moderate your emotions without blocking any of them out.

g.title: j3408179272
g.text: i wanna go see a dragon!! that sounds SO COOL

g.title: j1257619483
g.text: Without their support? I'd probably still be there. Endlessly looping. Endlessly dying. Indifferent to it all.

g.title: j3789709017
g.text: They gave me what I needed to achieve victory. Victory over myself. And hopefully, soon... the Indifference.

g.title: j3425137266
g.text: Strange, at first. But getting to fly? That's so much fun.

g.text: 我们俩是屠龙勇士！向胜利冲锋！

g.text: I just wish it lasted. And that it wasn't trying to actively *kill me.*

g.title: j3684999936
